This paper is about optimizing neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper specifically focuses on the optimization method called Kronecker-Factored Approximate Curvature (K-FAC), which is a technique that can be applied to various types of neural networks, including convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) models. Additionally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of K-FAC, which is a topic that falls under the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
